  "response_text": "To solve the equation \\(3x + 5 = 20\\) for \\(x\\), follow these steps:\n\n1. **Subtract 5 from both sides** of the equation to isolate the term with \\(x\\):\n   \\[\n   3x + 5 - 5 = 20 - 5\n   \\]\n   Simplifying this gives:\n   \\[\n   3x = 15\n   \\]\n\n2. **Divide both sides** of the equation by 3 to solve for \\(x\\):\n   \\[\n   \\frac{3x}{3} = \\frac{15}{3}\n   \\]\n   Simplifying this gives:\n   \\[\n   x = 5\n   \\]\n\nSo, the solution is \\(x = 5\\).",
